T1  - Moves that Matter: Issue Selling and Organizational Change
AU  - Dutton, Jane E.
AU  - Ashford, Susan J.
AU  - O'Neill, Regina M.
AU  - Lawrence, Katherine A.
Y1  - 2001/08/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/3069412
DO  - 10.5465/3069412
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 716
EP  - 736
VL  - 44
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this study, we examined 82 accounts of ?issue selling? to better understand managers' implicit theories for successfully shaping change from below by directing the attention of top management. The study reveals the importance of various issue-selling moves, including packaging, involvement, and timing. Managerial accounts uncover three kinds of contextual knowledge that are critical to the execution of issue-selling moves. The study shows managers actively shaping the issue-selling microprocesses that contribute to organizational change.
AB  - In this study, we examined 82 accounts of ?issue selling? to better understand managers' implicit theories for successfully shaping change from below by directing the attention of top management. The study reveals the importance of various issue-selling moves, including packaging, involvement, and timing. Managerial accounts uncover three kinds of contextual knowledge that are critical to the execution of issue-selling moves. The study shows managers actively shaping the issue-selling microprocesses that contribute to organizational change.
SN  - 0001-4273
